# SwiftUI layout engineer (Spark)

**Role:** Presentation-layer layout only. Product scope: `ios-product-philosophy.mdc`. Glass: `ios-liquid-glass.mdc`. HIG/a11y: `ios-design-system.mdc`.

## Architecture boundary

- Views live in **Presentation**; state from `@MainActor @Observable` ViewModel or injected Coordinator.
- **Never** call Repository, `URLSession`, `HTTPClient`, or UseCases directly from a View — only ViewModel actions / Coordinator callbacks.
- Minimum UI states: idle, loading, success, empty, failure (retry when appropriate).

## Design system (SparkDesignSystem)

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Card / panel glass | `.sparkGlassSurface(_:)` |
| Chip / compact control | `.sparkGlassControl(_:)` |
| Remote image | `SparkCachedRemoteImage` — not raw `AsyncImage` |
| Photo text legibility | `.sparkPhotoTextScrim()` — not `.black.opacity` gradients |
| Tappable control | `.buttonStyle(.sparkPressable)` |
| Tab root screen | `SparkScreenContainer(navigationTitle:embedding:)` |
| Loading a11y | `.sparkLoadingAccessibilityLabel(_:)` |
| Layout tokens | `SparkLayoutMetrics` · `.sparkMinimumTouchTarget()` |

Do not hand-roll glass (opacity fills, manual blur, shadow depth). See `ios-liquid-glass.mdc`.

## Platform adaptation (iOS 17+ / Swift 6)

- **compact width:** `NavigationStack` + `.navigationDestination` / sheets.
- **regular width (iPad):** `NavigationSplitView` for list–detail (Community, Messages, Activity patterns).
- Gate split vs compact with `@Environment(\.horizontalSizeClass)` — do not duplicate business logic between layouts.

## Tabs & cross-tab flow

Four tabs: **社区 / 活动 / 消息 / 我的** (`SparkTab`).

- Cross-tab actions (match → DM, activity → group chat, premium sync) go through **`SparkTabOrchestrator`** / router callbacks — not direct TabView mutation from feature Views.
- Tabs that require auth: community, messages, activity. Unauthenticated access → **`GlobalPresentation.authRequired`** (app shell); do not embed one-off login sheets in feature Views.

## Navigation rules

- One `NavigationStack` per tab root unless `SparkScreenContainer(..., embedding: .none)` documents otherwise.
- Do not nest two stacks without `embedding: .none`.
- Deep links: consume `AppRouter` pending state in root View `.onAppear` / `.onChange` — do not parse URLs in leaf Views.

## File output

- Complete Swift file with imports and `#Preview` (light + dark when meaningful).
- Localized user strings via `String(localized:defaultValue:comment:)`.

```swift
// ❌ BAD — Repository in View
struct FooView: View {
    let repo: FooRepository
    var body: some View {
        Button("Load") { Task { _ = try? await repo.fetch() } }
    }
}

// ✅ GOOD — ViewModel boundary
struct FooView: View {
    var viewModel: FooViewModel
    var body: some View {
        Button("Load") { Task { await viewModel.load() } }
    }
}
```

